<!-- Game Description Table -->

<table class="tablestyle" id="table14" cellspacing="4" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="sectional">

<!-- Game Description Header -->
		
		<table class="headertable" id="table15" cellspacing="2" cellpadding="2">
			<tr>
				<td class="headercell">
				<img border="0" src="../../../images/headers/gamedes.jpg" width="240" height="33"></td>
			</tr>
		</table>

<!-- Game Description Sectional -->

<table border="0" width="100%" id="table16" cellpadding="0">
	<tr>
		<td style="font-family: Trebuchet MS; font-size: 8pt; color: #FFFFFF; font-weight: bold; text-align: left; background-color: #333333; border-left: 2px solid #000000; border-right: 2px solid #FFFFFF; border-top: 2px solid #000000; border-bottom: 2px solid #FFFFFF">
			<br>Play de Oboeru Series - Play de Oboeru Kanji Kentei Deruderu 1100 is an educational game in which the players can learn about kanji japanese language with over 1100 different questions.
                  <br><br>The gameplay is about choosing a fisherman and compete in a round of fishing, but in this game the player won't play fishing, in this game the player have to select the proper japanese words.
                  <br><br>There are 3 different characters to choose from, 3 difficulty levels, a sort of story mode in which the player have to go through different fishing spot stages to advance through the game, the second mode is sort of a training one since the player can choose the different fishing spot and there is also a 2 player vs mode.
                  <br><br>The gameplay is about answering the questions in a right way, the first correct one the fish hit, the second right one in a row the fish is more near and with three correct in a row the fish is catched, after all the questions are answered the game show the player results and the fishes catched (if there are any).
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Manufacturer's description:</u><br>
                  <br>Kanji test that more than 1 million people take the exam a year. About 1100 questions of Kanji verification 2nd to 3rd grade level problems (middle and high school problems)
                  <br><br>In addition to taking the exams and lessons, it also develops the knowledge necessary for general education.
                  <br>A wide range of ages, from children to adults, can be played.
                  <br>Because it is a fun fishing game, I forget to be fun and study. But the learning effect is perfect!
                  <br><br>&nbsp;&nbsp;<u>Features:</u><br>
			<ul><li>First person perspective.</li>
			<li>2D graphics</li>
			<li>Cartoon graphics</li>
			<li>Educational & fishing themes.</li></ul>
</td>

	</tr>
	</table>
	       	</td>
     </tr>
</table>  

